# Project Overview

Personal portfolio for a Software Engineer at AWS (API Gateway). Dark-first, single-page design with smooth animations.

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| Framework | Next.js 16 (App Router) + TypeScript |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS v4 + Shadcn/UI (new-york style) |
| Animations | Framer Motion |
| Icons | Lucide React |
| Forms | React Hook Form + Zod (via `@hookform/resolvers`) |
| Theming | next-themes (class strategy, dark default, system-aware) |
| Utilities | clsx + tailwind-merge via `cn()` in `src/lib/utils.ts` |

## Directory Structure

```
src/
├── app/                  # Next.js App Router (layout, page, globals.css)
├── components/
│   ├── ui/               # Shadcn/UI primitives (button, input, textarea, label)
│   ├── sections/         # Page sections (hero, experience, projects, education, contact)
│   ├── navbar.tsx         # Sticky header with mobile hamburger + theme toggle
│   ├── footer.tsx         # Copyright + social icon links
│   ├── contact-form.tsx   # RHF + Zod validated form
│   └── theme-provider.tsx # next-themes wrapper
├── data/                 # Static data as typed TypeScript arrays
│   ├── experience.ts
│   ├── projects.ts
│   ├── education.ts
│   └── social.ts
└── lib/
    ├── utils.ts           # cn() helper
    └── schemas.ts         # Zod validation schemas
```

## Key Conventions

- All imports use the `@/` alias (maps to `./src/*`)
- Components use named exports, not default exports
- Client components start with `"use client"` directive
- Data files export both the interface and the data array
- Content max-width is `857px` (`max-w-[857px]`), matching the Figma artboard
- Section horizontal padding: `px-6 lg:px-12`
